5W</a></p><p> - Power 105.1 (@Power1051) <a href="https://twitter.com/Power1051/status/1826251122643779601?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">2024 年 8 月 21 日</a></p></blockquote><p><script async src="https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script></p><p></p><p>去年，<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/will-i-am-wants-to-protect-his-facial-math-from-ai-3446793">Will.i.am 通过<em>Sirius XM 的</em>亮相分享了他对人工智能是否正在造福音乐产业的看法</a>。作为回应，这位<a href="https://www.nme.com/tag/grammys">格莱美</a>奖获得者表示：“我们都有声音，但每个人都受到了妥协，因为你的面部数学或你的声音频率没有任何权利或所有权。”</p><p>他解释了自己的愤世嫉俗，并补充道：“你接到 FaceTime 或 Zoom 通话，由于通话中没有任何智能，因此无法验证人工智能通话或个人通话的身份。”</p><p>他继续说道：“保护我们的面部数学是当务之急。我就是我的脸数学。我不拥有那个。我拥有《I Got A Feeling》的权利，我拥有我写的歌曲的权利，但我不拥有我的脸或我的声音的权利？” </p><figure id="attachment_3568588" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3568588" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-3568588" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/will-i-am-Kym-Illman-Getty-Images-@2000x1270.jpg" alt="威尔.我.照片来源：Kym Illman/Getty Images" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/will-i-am-Kym-Illman-Getty-Images-@2000x1270.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/will-i-am-Kym-Illman-Getty-Images-@2000x1270-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/will-i-am-Kym-Illman-Getty-Images-@2000x1270-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/will-i-am-Kym-Illman-Getty-Images-@2000x1270-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/will-i-am-Kym-Illman-Getty-Images-@2000x1270-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/will-i-am-Kym-Illman-Getty-Images-@2000x1270-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3568588" class="wp-caption-text">威尔.我.照片来源：Kym Illman/Getty Images</figcaption></figure><p>这一消息发布之际，人工智能在音乐行业中的作用越来越受到争议。本月早些时候，<a href="https://www.nme.com/tag/k-pop">韩国流行</a>娱乐巨头<a href="https://www.nme.com/brands/sm-entertainment">SM Entertainment</a>宣布<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/sm-entertainment-debut-first-ai-singer-naevis-3785500">其第一位人工智能生成歌手 nævis 即将首次亮相</a>。</p><p>今年早些时候，包括<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/billie-eilish">Billie Eilish</a> 、 <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/robert-smith">Robert Smith</a> 、 <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/stevie-wonder">Stevie Wonder</a>和<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/nicki-minaj">Nicki Minaj</a>在内的 200 多名艺术家<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/billie-eilish-robert-smith-more-sign-open-letter-against-predatory-use-of-ai-in-music-3612507">签署了一封由艺术家权利联盟编写的公开信</a>，警告不要在音乐中“掠夺性”使用人工智能。</p><p>许多<a href="https://www.nme.com/tag/hip-hop">嘻哈</a>传奇人物也参与了人工智能音乐辩论。制作人<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/timbaland">Timbaland</a> <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/timbaland-previews-new-song-with-an-ai-generated-notorious-b-i-g-verse-3439869">预览了人工智能生成的</a><a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/notorious-b-i-g">Notorious BIG</a>诗句，并正在开发人工智能软件以将这种现象商业化。然而， <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/snoop-dogg">Snoop Dogg</a>表示，人工智能音乐在<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/michael-jackson">迈克尔·杰克逊</a>人工智能翻唱<a href="https://www.nme.com/blogs/nme-blogs/who-is-c-murder-no-limit-chronicles-rapper-kim-kardashian-prison-master-p-2731036">C-Murder</a>的《Down With My N&#39;s》方面<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/snoop-dogg-says-a-i-music-is-outta-hand-michael-jackson-3438896">已经“失控”</a> 。</p><p>最近，<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/sting">斯汀</a>表示人工智能“没有给他留下深刻的印象”， <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/sting-says-songwriting-battle-between-humans-and-ai-is-coming-3445016">歌曲作者必须捍卫“我们的人力资本免受人工智能的侵害”。</a>然而， <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/smashing-pumpkins">Smashing Pumpkins</a>的<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/billy-corgan">Billy Corgan</a>表示<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/smashing-pumpkins-billy-corgan-says-ai-will-change-music-forever-3446083">“人工智能将永远改变音乐”，</a>因为其他人可以“玩弄系统”并且“不会在地下室度过 10,000 个小时”。</p><p> <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/peter-hook">Peter Hook</a>还针对<a href="https://www.nme.com/tag/ai">人工智能</a>创作的歌曲表示，创作出来的每一首歌都是“狗屎”。</p><p>然而，最多产的艺术家发声实例之一来自<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/nick-cave-and-the-bad-seeds">Bad Seeds</a>主唱<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/nick-cave">尼克·凯夫 (Nick Cave)</a> ，他<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/nick-cave-calls-chatgpt-and-ai-songwriting-a-grotesque-mockery-of-what-it-is-to-be-human-3381620">将这一概念描述为“对人类本质的怪诞嘲讽”</a> 。他后来补充说<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/nick-cave-chatgpt-should-just-fuck-off-and-leave-songwriting-alone-3421859">，他希望像 ChatGPT 这样的人工智能平台“滚蛋，别管歌曲创作了”</a> 。 </p><figure id="attachment_3774404" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3774404" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-3774404" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Nick-Cave-Photo-by-Andreas-Rentz_Getty-Images.jpg" alt="尼克·凯夫" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Nick-Cave-Photo-by-Andreas-Rentz_Getty-Images.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Nick-Cave-Photo-by-Andreas-Rentz_Getty-Images-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Nick-Cave-Photo-by-Andreas-Rentz_Getty-Images-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Nick-Cave-Photo-by-Andreas-Rentz_Getty-Images-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Nick-Cave-Photo-by-Andreas-Rentz_Getty-Images-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/Nick-Cave-Photo-by-Andreas-Rentz_Getty-Images-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3774404" class="wp-caption-text">尼克·凯夫（Nick Cave）——图片来源：Andreas Rentz/Getty Images</figcaption></figure><p>同样，枪花乐队成员<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/slash">Slash</a>和<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/duff-mckagan">Duff McKagan</a>也参与了这场辩论，前者表示该技术的使用<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/slash-says-that-use-of-ai-in-music-does-not-really-thrill-me-3759692">“并没有真正令我兴奋”</a> ，后者<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/duff-mckagan-not-worried-about-ai-in-music-its-not-gonna-affect-my-creativity-3511911">告诉<em>NME</em> ，他不打算让人工智能“影响我的创造力”</a> 。</p><p><a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/heres-a-lost-oasis-album-created-by-ai-3432125">在英国乐队使用人工智能想象英国流行音乐偶像如果要改革并发行新专辑时会是什么样子后，</a>前绿洲成员也发表了讲话。</p><p>当时， <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/liam-gallagher-responds-to-lost-oasis-album-made-by-ai-2-3432480">利亚姆 (Liam) 对他所听到的这张专辑表示欢迎</a>，写道：“它比市面上所有其他的专辑都要好，”而<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/noel-gallagher">诺埃尔·加拉格尔 (Noel Gallagher)</a>在接受<em><a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/noel-gallagher-responds-to-the-ai-generated-lost-oasis-album-3451406">NME</a></em> <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/noel-gallagher-responds-to-the-ai-generated-lost-oasis-album-3451406">采访时</a>表示：“这些该死的白痴显然花了太多时间在他们的专辑上。”手和太多的钱，他们可以负担得起这项技术，为了搞笑而做这些事。”</p><p>格莱姆斯尤其直言不讳地表达了她对不断发展的音乐技术（包括人工智能）的支持。去年，她向粉丝们<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/grimes-is-beta-testing-her-own-ai-voice-mimicking-software-3438652" target="_blank" rel="noopener">表示</a><a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/grimes-is-beta-testing-her-own-ai-voice-mimicking-software-3438652">祝福，只要她能获得歌曲版税的一半，就可以用她的声音通过人工智能创作新音乐</a>，就像她与任何与她合作的艺术家一样。</p><p>在 Will.i.am 的其他新闻中，他最近透露<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/U2">U2</a>是<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/will-i-am-on-how-u2-inspired-black-eyed-peas-i-gotta-feeling-i-wrote-the-chorus-for-them-3782278">黑眼豆豆热门歌曲《I Gotta Feeling》的灵感来源，这位音乐家称他“为他们写了副歌”</a> 。</p><p> <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/will-i-am-launches-ai-driven-radio-3787075">Will.I.Am 推出人工智能广播的</a>帖子首先出现在<a href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a>上。</p> ;
